                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-363" type="surname" value="LEVERETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460223-name-363" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL LEVERETT</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Walworth—I have known the prisoner four or five years—on the 30th of Jan. I took a mare to Smithfield-market—I saw the prisoner there—I asked him to get on the back of the mare, and ride it backwards and forwards—just as we were coming out of the market I sold it to a man—I told the prisoner to take it to my house—I went home in a <hi rend="italic">cab</hi> with the man I was going to sell the mare to, and the prisoner had not taken</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184602230087"></xptr>
               <p>it home—I never saw him again till he was in custody—I found the mare at Lewisham, a fortnight ago last Friday.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was waiting to sell the mare; I did not know who it belonged to.</p>
